text: Elizabeth Fitzgerald Stemke (born July 15, 1980) is an American volleyball player and coach. She was a member of the United States women's national volleyball team. She participated at the 2002 Women's Volleyball World Championships and 2003 Pan-American Games. == Life == She graduated from University of Wisconsin. She coached for University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill. == References == Category:1980 births Category:Living people Category:American volleyball players Category:American volleyball coaches
